Wash and dry all produce. Preheat #oven{} to 400 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of water to a boil. Add @brown rice{3/4%cup} and cook until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Drain.

Place @cashew pieces{1%ounce} on a #baking sheet{}, and toast in oven until fragrant, about ~{5%minutes}. Remove from sheet and set aside.

> TIP: Keep an eye on these so they don't burn!

Peel and finely dice @carrot{1}(peeled and finely diced). Trim and cut @green beans{6%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), keeping greens and whites separate. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Peel and finely mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}(finely minced or grated). Drain half of @corn{1%can}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add carrots and toss until slightly softened, about ~{5%minutes}. Add green beans and corn, and toss until green beans are crisp-tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add garlic and ginger. Cook ~{1%minute}, until fragrant. Add cooked rice and toss until slightly crispy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add cooked veggies, @soy sauce{4%tablespoons}, and scallion whites. Toss another ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide rice between bowls. Sprinkle with cashews, @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}, and scallion greens.